Japanese Bought Net 38.2 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-08-31T23:57:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/japanese-bought-net-38-2-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Aug. 26 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 38.2 billion yen ($497.6 million)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 146.3 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 57.2 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 127.4 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 138.5 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 338 billion yen in stocks, and sold 504.5 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 981
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  